The paper deals with mobile malware infection rates and risk indicators, which are topics related to computer security (cs.CR) and software engineering (cs.SE). The study also involves data analysis and machine learning techniques to identify infected devices, which falls under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses the impact of malware on device performance, which could be classified under cyber-physical systems (cs.CY) or multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
